{"questionId":"10123","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1a\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">Write down these three equations as a matrix equation.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Evidence of attempting to set up a matrix equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong> </em></p>\n<p>Correct <strong>matrix</strong> equation representing the given equations&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A2&nbsp; &nbsp;N3 </strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {27}&amp;9&amp;3 \\\\   1&amp;1&amp;1 \\\\   { - 1}&amp;1&amp;{ - 1}  \\end{array}} \\right)\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  m \\\\   n \\\\   p  \\end{array}} \\right) = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {18} \\\\   0 \\\\   { - 10}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>27</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>9</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>p</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>18</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10123","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.8d.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down these three equations as a matrix equation.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}